:class:`~icalendar.prop.binary.vBinary` now stores the raw ``bytes`` of the value internally, so non-UTF-8 binary data round-trips losslessly. With the release of icalendar 7.1.0, and previous to this bug fix, :attr:`vBinary.ical_value <icalendar.prop.binary.vBinary.ical_value>` Base64-decoded the raw stored bytes and raised :class:`ValueError` for non-Base64 input. :attr:`vBinary.ical_value <icalendar.prop.binary.vBinary.ical_value>` now returns the raw stored bytes instead of Base64-decoding them, and no longer raises :class:`ValueError` for non-Base64 input. @uwezkhan
